{
  "id": "RAW_1fa062",
  "title": "GPT-5 视觉能力评估：前沿视觉推理模型，但非 SOTA",
  "url": "https://www.latent.space/p/gpt5-vision",
  "date": "2025-08-07 21:36:49",
  "author": "Matvei Popov",
  "siteName": "Latent Space",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <div dir=\"auto\" class=\"body markup\">\n   <p><em><span>Editor’s note: Welcome Matvei of </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/2024-vision?utm_source=publication-search\" rel=\"\">Roboflow</a><span> to the Latent Space guest author crew! notice how GPT-5-Mini’s vision scores the same as GPT-5’s vision. This is </span><a href=\"https://www.latent.space/p/gpt5-router\" rel=\"\">an expected consequence of a very good model router at work</a><span>.</span></em></p>\n   <p><span>Something that went under the radar in OpenAI’s release today is GPT-5’s vision and visual reasoning capabilities. Adding visual understanding to LLMs has proven to be difficult, with </span><a href=\"https://blog.roboflow.com/gpt-4o-vision-use-cases/\" rel=\"\">most models not being able to correctly count 4 coins in a photo</a><span> or locate where specific items are in an image.</span></p>\n   <p><span>LLMs being able to understand the world around them in real-time is the breakthrough people are looking for to enable the autonomous robotics or computer-using revolution and open up the </span><a href=\"https://www.meta.com/superintelligence/?srsltid=AfmBOoocENSXCjtFmlqet6AfR37CTc22DUrxFXYvKb8d8-gz4uTqEr5A\" rel=\"\">era of personal superintelligence</a><span>.</span></p>\n   <p></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">Current state of LLMs and visual understanding \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/170397683/current-state-of-llms-and-visual-understanding\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p>The combination of reasoning and visual capabilities has been present in several models like OpenAI GPT and o series models, Google’s Gemini models, Anthropic’s Claude models, and Meta’s Llama models. Models tend to have specific strengths and weaknesses depending on the task type:</p>\n   <ul>\n    <li>\n     <p>Tasks like reading text, signs, receipts, CAPTCHAs, and understanding colors are generally solved by all models.</p></li>\n    <li>\n     <p><span>But harder tasks, like </span><strong>counting, spatial understanding, object detection, and document understanding have high levels of performance variability, </strong><span>especially if it is known to be deficient in most internet-scale pretrain data.</span></p>\n     <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n      <figure>\n       <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!zpiY!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F61253bad-582a-478e-adc5-6e91e18ccc6a_1750x1335.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n        <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n         <picture>\n          <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/b61be7ad-7e69-406a-9ca2-1313864ccd00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9dcf3908-ca61-486d-17a4-357830e68700/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/838bdcae-fce6-4665-e226-b90095cf6b00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c382ec23-3249-49ad-ad69-b91f1fd73d00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n          <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/d5d3c953-0a3e-4644-055a-69ab49c90900/public\" width=\"468\" height=\"357.10714285714283\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/61253bad-582a-478e-adc5-6e91e18ccc6a_1750x1335.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1111,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:468,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/35ca50cc-a8ff-4d8f-0126-d3ab5e539600/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/e98834da-ee25-486b-00b4-c820e69a8200/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/339d86c1-14e8-4c25-edef-c3f146f17700/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/d5d3c953-0a3e-4644-055a-69ab49c90900/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" fetchpriority=\"high\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n         </picture>\n         <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n          <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n           <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container restack-image\">\n            <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-refresh-cw\">\n             <path d=\"M3 12a9 9 0 0 1 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1 6.74 2.74L21 8\"></path><path d=\"M21 3v5h-5\"></path><path d=\"M21 12a9 9 0 0 1-9 9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1-6.74-2.74L3 16\"></path><path d=\"M8 16H3v5\"></path>\n            </svg>\n           </div>\n           <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container view-image\">\n            <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\">\n             <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n            </svg>\n           </div>\n          </div>\n         </div>\n        </div></a>\n       <figcaption class=\"image-caption\">\n        <a href=\"https://rf100-vl.org/\" rel=\"\">from RF100VL</a>\n       </figcaption>\n      </figure>\n     </div></li>\n   </ul>\n   <p><span>The variance across tasks types makes general comparison difficult but that’s why leaderboards, like </span><a href=\"https://visioncheckup.com\" rel=\"\">Vision Checkup</a><span>, have recently launched. Vision Checkup is our </span><a href=\"https://github.com/roboflow/vision-ai-checkup\" rel=\"\">open source</a><span> vision model evaluation leaderboard and it gives us insight into hard task frontier performance. As you can see, OpenAI dominates in vision capabilities and the launch of </span><strong>GPT-5 adds another model into the top 5</strong><span>.</span></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!gaT-!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcb180286-1702-49ed-916d-ddfdceaf24b3_1288x954.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/dbfa8417-c651-4ae6-bd0c-c91c9601a300/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/3f3a7821-f5d2-427a-48fd-c26cecdd8300/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/53d52828-d8ab-4ac1-dc9c-517a0fddfd00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/28f9997e-2d4b-4222-7101-63866ed8ff00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/e53a691e-1419-4c80-72ef-bb786449d500/public\" width=\"1288\" height=\"954\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/cb180286-1702-49ed-916d-ddfdceaf24b3_1288x954.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:954,&quot;width&quot;:1288,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:313174,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/170397683?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcb180286-1702-49ed-916d-ddfdceaf24b3_1288x954.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/dc673d80-fa8d-4639-cde8-4a128c35a200/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5a9d048b-685d-4c32-a863-ff87025c4300/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/bc381bff-2813-4105-09e4-a9927f67b000/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/e53a691e-1419-4c80-72ef-bb786449d500/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-refresh-cw\">\n           <path d=\"M3 12a9 9 0 0 1 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1 6.74 2.74L21 8\"></path><path d=\"M21 3v5h-5\"></path><path d=\"M21 12a9 9 0 0 1-9 9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1-6.74-2.74L3 16\"></path><path d=\"M8 16H3v5\"></path>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div></a>\n     <figcaption class=\"image-caption\">\n      note that mini perfoms the same as main! good job, router\n     </figcaption>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>The leaderboard makes it clear – top models are all reasoning models.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">Reasoning is driving OpenAI dominance in general vision tasks \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/170397683/reasoning-is-driving-openai-dominance-in-general-vision-tasks\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p>The top models on the Vision Checkup leaderboard are configurations of models with reasoning capabilities.</p>\n   <p><span>We suspect that the good results of these models can be attributed more to their reasoning capabilities from pretraining and during test time. </span><strong>This marks the continuation of an important development in multi-modal large language models: the ability to reason over both text and vision modalities.</strong></p>\n   <p>With that said, scores vary significantly between updates and you can attribute this to multiple reasons. The biggest one is the nondeterminism of reasoning mode for OpenAI models; prompting a reasoning model with the same question twice can lead to both correct and incorrect answers.</p>\n   <p>When it comes to real-world use, reasoning on images currently takes too much time to be useful and variability of answers makes them difficult to rely on. For most developers, 10+ seconds to understand an image won’t unlock real time use cases. There is a trade off to be made between speed and capability. Depending on the task, a faster model with a more narrow range of knowledge could be the best decision.</p>\n   <p></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">Beyond Vision Vibe Checks \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/170397683/beyond-vision-vibe-checks\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p>We are still far from a world where autonomous robotics can interact with the world around them in real time. Simple tasks like counting, spatial understanding, and object localization are key for any robot to perform general tasks outside of a controlled environment.</p>\n   <p><span>To get us beyond leaderboards with lightweight vibe checks, we need to test LLMs across a wide range of domains and track their progress. We released a new benchmark, </span><a href=\"https://rf100-vl.org/\" rel=\"\">RF100-VL</a><span>, at this year’s CVPR conference to provide a more difficult set of visual understanding and grounding benchmarks. The benchmark asks “How well does your LLM understand the real world?”. RF100-VL consists of 100 open source datasets from the Roboflow Universe community containing object detection bounding boxes and multimodal few shot instruction with visual examples and rich textual descriptions across novel image domains.</span></p>\n   <p><span>The top LLMs scored below 10 mAP50:95 for identifying novel objects in real world contexts. The current SOTA among all LLMs is Gemini 2.5 Pro, achieving a zero-shot mAP50:95 of </span><strong>13.3</strong><span>:</span></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!LmtU!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4b035d53-039d-4852-9df2-3d66724f7b76_1568x780.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0aed9a73-1640-403c-d9de-bb7cb6648500/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0b238c0a-c38e-415e-5b3b-fa0aeb2c0b00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5ec3104e-f6b7-4e15-4c71-f87fec7fe900/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5e462a8b-7562-442b-0e9e-1864e4a0ed00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/31d4b7b5-9b89-4be0-7dc1-80a3b3af4200/public\" width=\"1200\" height=\"596.7032967032967\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/4b035d53-039d-4852-9df2-3d66724f7b76_1568x780.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:false,&quot;imageSize&quot;:&quot;large&quot;,&quot;height&quot;:724,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:1200,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:&quot;center&quot;,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c9a846f2-c758-47c4-e40b-259d390d5e00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5e5ae427-ffb1-40a3-48b1-5be85139dd00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/b9b3119a-61b8-4b1b-5ac1-8c4152545700/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/8f387c9a-d12d-4a2f-eb7c-f7564b193200/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-large\">\n       </picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-refresh-cw\">\n           <path d=\"M3 12a9 9 0 0 1 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1 6.74 2.74L21 8\"></path><path d=\"M21 3v5h-5\"></path><path d=\"M21 12a9 9 0 0 1-9 9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1-6.74-2.74L3 16\"></path><path d=\"M8 16H3v5\"></path>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>We suspect that the key distinction between OpenAI models and models like Gemini or Qwen, when it comes to object detection tasks, is that OpenAI models don’t include any object detection data in their pretraining.</p>\n   <p><span>After running GPT-5 on RF100-VL we got the</span><strong> mAP50:95 of 1.5</strong><span>. This is significantly lower than the current SOTA of </span><strong>Gemini 2.5 Pro of 13.3</strong><span>. We largely attribute this shortcoming to lack of object detection pre-training for GPT-5.</span></p>\n   <p>Let’s inspect some of its results below to develop more intuition into why the score may be so low.</p>\n   <p></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">Example: Localization \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/170397683/example-localization\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p>This is an example from a volleyball dataset, which demonstrates the key issue causing low scores. We observe that the model has a good understanding of objects in the images, you can see it correctly understanding that there is a ball, two blockers, and some defenders present.</p>\n   <p>However it is unable to localize them, all of the boxes are not matching the objects locations and sizes. It seems like the model is good at understanding the image, but not good at grounding the specific objects within it, which again we attribute to lack of object detection tasks in pre-training.</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!DfTR!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4582b797-de6e-410e-ac01-d92d623c05ef_1600x900.jpeg\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/47c9a3e4-ae0b-4da7-0ebf-cf4d26dbfe00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/082b8631-f77f-42a6-d715-3f83df5bbd00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/6e88a26c-ba2d-41e1-c6fa-6e0daf811000/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0f1b95a7-a646-4622-6ddf-9b4839726500/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/a299a456-538d-401b-cf99-df936741ac00/public\" width=\"1456\" height=\"819\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/4582b797-de6e-410e-ac01-d92d623c05ef_1600x900.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:819,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0023663b-349d-4e86-95da-d5504c2a3300/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/dffeb31d-0f5b-4671-65d7-85438e137200/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c1eaa92b-3d01-4581-fa3f-065d77052a00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/a299a456-538d-401b-cf99-df936741ac00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-refresh-cw\">\n           <path d=\"M3 12a9 9 0 0 1 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1 6.74 2.74L21 8\"></path><path d=\"M21 3v5h-5\"></path><path d=\"M21 12a9 9 0 0 1-9 9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1-6.74-2.74L3 16\"></path><path d=\"M8 16H3v5\"></path>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>We can see a similar situation with a sheep dataset below:</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!GLPx!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fefc9a43a-6644-4161-b30a-1b060aeda132_1600x900.jpeg\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/29c2a4d2-0cb4-4696-23a4-0eeb223db900/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/68f69104-f674-4cfe-7918-e7de00957e00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/65f689d8-923d-47fa-64bd-04c9fcc78400/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c7b2648c-ebd2-4094-964f-8aba18a12300/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/24f3d08d-067c-4e23-2610-7bb62c261f00/public\" width=\"1456\" height=\"819\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/efc9a43a-6644-4161-b30a-1b060aeda132_1600x900.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:819,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/7334ed34-48c6-4e3b-0397-f5563c000c00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/e72b5d5e-c346-40c6-8352-647130fea700/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ea3aada4-e207-4a90-9ff5-786e65bd8000/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/24f3d08d-067c-4e23-2610-7bb62c261f00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-refresh-cw\">\n           <path d=\"M3 12a9 9 0 0 1 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1 6.74 2.74L21 8\"></path><path d=\"M21 3v5h-5\"></path><path d=\"M21 12a9 9 0 0 1-9 9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1-6.74-2.74L3 16\"></path><path d=\"M8 16H3v5\"></path>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p></p>\n   <h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\">Example: UI Elements \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/170397683/example-ui-elements\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h2>\n   <p>With recent developments in LLMs for tool use and vision-powered agentic workflows, let's look at GPT-5 performance there. We don’t see any uplift in quality in the UI elements dataset either:</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!lfBY!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3b74643c-6334-44f3-9b82-cec6ac1cb6ce_400x865.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ff375403-aa6c-4eec-1684-4d0339a78900/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c0fcc272-bca2-4143-124e-6593f1b1b600/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/66bb7ed9-9c47-4022-6594-f97f9a819d00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/f82ae33a-957a-4710-a819-3c1f85545600/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c1193f3d-3b61-4eb2-f305-f265163e3300/public\" width=\"400\" height=\"865\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/3b74643c-6334-44f3-9b82-cec6ac1cb6ce_400x865.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:865,&quot;width&quot;:400,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:null,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:null,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/835177ea-e4f3-4610-d455-5af416138300/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/a0aca437-ad02-4b69-8879-468a607e7f00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/e939a144-f686-4ff6-622a-1cd27a147800/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c1193f3d-3b61-4eb2-f305-f265163e3300/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n       <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n        <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container restack-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-refresh-cw\">\n           <path d=\"M3 12a9 9 0 0 1 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1 6.74 2.74L21 8\"></path><path d=\"M21 3v5h-5\"></path><path d=\"M21 12a9 9 0 0 1-9 9 9.75 9.75 0 0 1-6.74-2.74L3 16\"></path><path d=\"M8 16H3v5\"></path>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"pencraft pc-reset icon-container view-image\">\n          <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2\">\n           <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n          </svg>\n         </div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p>Next up, let’s see if GPT5 is better compared to previous OpenAI models:</p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!0QYS!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5d0aba0f-c3f6-422a-9cb1-2422a957b9e9_1664x292.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/077fd9d3-d3dc-4f05-a1d4-42c136594900/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c55d1538-d857-4c3a-3088-9a941c285000/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/648744ed-5906-4af9-281c-c14c60d16a00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/dfb733e2-b0bd-4299-62f5-effdc3c86700/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/15887d01-0fff-4826-f703-ab0557886400/public\" width=\"1456\" height=\"256\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/5d0aba0f-c3f6-422a-9cb1-2422a957b9e9_1664x292.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:256,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:35074,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/170397683?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5d0aba0f-c3f6-422a-9cb1-2422a957b9e9_1664x292.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/a62f3ede-5ffb-4493-c527-cf23e131d900/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/bb8a057f-8c9d-4a20-54de-4a4a029a1500/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/eb276dbe-50e4-4788-a885-2226fe346400/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/15887d01-0fff-4826-f703-ab0557886400/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p></p>\n   <p>GPT-5 has gotten slightly better than o3. And in both cases providing additional information, such as detailed instructions, helps the model.</p>\n   <p><span>Interestingly, changing the reasoning effort to high doesn’t improve the scores for </span><a href=\"https://rf100-vl.org/\" rel=\"\">RF100-VL</a><span>. So the benefit of reasoning is not as obvious in the RF100-VL case and suspect it to be due to lack of object detection capabilities, arising from lack of object detection tasks in the pretraining.</span></p>\n   <p></p>\n   <h1 class=\"header-anchor-post\">GPT-5 is a slight improvement for simple visual tasks \n    <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent\">\n     <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA\">\n      <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" aria-label=\"Link\" data-href=\"https://www.latent.space/i/170397683/gpt-is-a-slight-improvement-for-simple-visual-tasks\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o\">\n       <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-link\">\n        <path d=\"M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71\"></path><path d=\"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71\"></path>\n       </svg></button>\n     </div>\n    </div></h1>\n   <p>GPT-5’s enhanced reasoning brings it high up on the Vision Checkup leaderboard, proving that multi-step thinking lets a model squeeze more juice out of the pixels. A great outcome for everyday use cases that people are likely relying on ChatGPT to help them solve.</p>\n   <p><a href=\"https://rf100-vl.org/\" rel=\"\">RF100-VL</a><span> helps highlight that comprehension ≠ localization. Without object-detection priors, the detections still miss the mark. Even so, GPT-5’s jump in vision-reasoning spotlights a clear path forward: models that don’t just see better but think more deeply about what they’re seeing.</span></p>\n   <p><span>Vision AI Engineers can see a more in-depth post on </span><a href=\"https://blog.roboflow.com/gpt-5-vision-multimodal-evaluation/\" rel=\"\">their blog</a><span>:</span></p>\n   <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n    <figure>\n     <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://blog.roboflow.com/gpt-5-vision-multimodal-evaluation/\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\" rel=\"\" class=\"image-link image2\">\n      <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n       <picture>\n        <source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/39e1603c-f6a5-46b1-a13f-678d4967ef00/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/7e6771c4-2558-4f94-f009-2ff3c7117d00/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/3d0db33f-50d6-43bc-a710-b7432d538d00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/524b1718-cb51-44b0-112d-86ddb0f24a00/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\">\n        <img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9305b4dd-4e86-43fa-3bea-ffaf52bd0600/public\" width=\"1200\" height=\"731\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7933bc6e-c02b-440e-b94b-ab9d8e871472_1200x731.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:731,&quot;width&quot;:1200,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:683076,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://blog.roboflow.com/gpt-5-vision-multimodal-evaluation/&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://www.latent.space/i/170397683?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7933bc6e-c02b-440e-b94b-ab9d8e871472_1200x731.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/85343713-9906-4dd3-4b17-75813d82d100/public 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/289b9793-ffd4-4ec6-9a0e-0d6a8960b500/public 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/55ba3b6c-173b-4450-126a-a3f1da36b300/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/9305b4dd-4e86-43fa-3bea-ffaf52bd0600/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"sizing-normal\">\n       </picture>\n      </div></a>\n    </figure>\n   </div>\n   <p></p>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "本文评估了 GPT-5 的视觉能力，强调其强大的推理能力，但在精确目标定位方面存在局限性，主要原因可能是缺乏目标检测相关的预训练。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "本文评估了 GPT-5 的视觉能力，强调其强大的推理能力，但在精确目标定位方面存在局限性，主要原因可能是缺乏目标检测相关的预训练。",
  "summary": "本文深入探讨了 OpenAI 的 GPT-5 视觉和视觉推理能力，该功能在其发布时未引起广泛关注。文章指出，虽然 LLM 通常可以处理基本的视觉任务（如文本识别），但在计数、空间理解和目标检测等复杂任务方面表现不佳。作者介绍了 Vision Checkup 排行榜，包括 GPT-5 在内的 OpenAI 模型在通用视觉任务中表现出色，这归功于它们的推理能力。然而，使用更严格的 RF100-VL 基准测试，GPT-5 的 mAP50:95 得分 (1.5) 明显低于当前的 SOTA Gemini 2.5 Pro (13.3)。这种差异主要归因于 GPT-5 无法准确地定位目标，尽管它理解目标的存在，这表明缺乏目标检测预训练。文章总结道，GPT-5 增强的推理能力对日常用例有益，但其在目标定位方面的局限性使其无法成为实际目标检测和代理工作流程的 SOTA。因此，需要像 RF100-VL 这样强大的基准来推动前沿模型的发展。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "GPT-5 展示了强大的视觉推理能力，但在精确的目标定位方面表现不佳。",
      "explanation": "尽管 GPT-5 在通用视觉任务中表现出色，但在 RF100-VL 等高级基准测试中无法准确定位目标，这表明其能力存在差距，可能是由于目标检测预训练不足。"
    },
    {
      "point": "目前的 LLM 在计数和空间理解等复杂视觉任务中面临重大挑战。",
      "explanation": "许多大型语言模型在“更难”的视觉任务中表现出很高的性能差异，这表明与物理世界的稳健实时交互需要的不仅仅是通用的视觉理解。"
    },
    {
      "point": "新的、严格的基准测试对于评估前沿视觉模型在现实世界中的理解能力至关重要。",
      "explanation": "传统的排行榜可能无法完全捕捉模型的局限性。像 RF100-VL 这样的基准测试可以对模型在不同真实环境上下理解和定位目标的能力进行更具挑战性和实用性的评估。"
    }
  ],
  "keyQuotes": [
    "但在计数、空间理解、目标检测和文档理解等更困难的任务中，模型性能差异很大，尤其是在缺乏大规模互联网预训练数据的情况下。",
    "这标志着多模态大型语言模型中一个重要发展的延续：能够对文本和视觉模式进行推理。",
    "我们怀疑 OpenAI 模型与 Gemini 或 Qwen 等模型在目标检测任务中的关键区别在于，OpenAI 模型在其预训练中不包含任何目标检测数据。",
    "RF100-VL 有助于强调理解 ≠ 定位。",
    "缺乏目标检测先验知识，会导致检测效果不佳。"
